  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Basic "Chicken" Broth</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Soups</cat>
        <cat>Vegetarian</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Water, boiling</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Corn oil</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Nutritional yeast (or more)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Poultry seasoning  (or more)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Mushrooms; chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Onions; finely chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Vegetable broth powder or bouillon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Onion salt to taste</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Stir ingredients together for an instant broth. Use in recipes calling for
  chicken stock, and as a basis for chickenless noodle or rice soup.
  
  For a basic "chicken" gravy, use the above recipe, stirring in flour at
  medium to low heat until desired thickness is reached. Delicious over
  mashed potatoes, stuffing and rice.
  
